  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (expanded envelope)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Following regulatory feedback, the operating envelope was extended post-validation to include a paediatric sub-population (body surface area < 0.6 m²) operating at reduced flow rates (0.8–1.5 L/min). The existing validation campaign, conducted exclusively on adult flow conditions (2.0–6.0 L/min), is considered by the assessment team to provide adequate coverage through engineering extrapolation; no new experimental validation data have been acquired for the paediatric regime.",
